			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    <B>* Everlore's Guide to Advanced Blacksmithing -- Updated</B></b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:BrandonP@obsidian-tech.com">Dieciden (Brandon Parker)</a> | 
		            9/13/2000 12:14:41 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2"><p><font face="verdana" size="2"><table border="0" cellspacing="1" width="100%">
    <tr>
      <td>

<p><b><a name="Advanced Blacksmithing:"><font face="Verdana" size="3">Advanced
Blacksmithing</font></a></b>
</font>
<b><a name="Advanced Blacksmithing:"><font face="Verdana" size="3">
(Updated):</font></a></b></p>

<p><b><font face="Verdana" size="3"> </font><font face="Verdana" size="2">**Updated
by <a href="mailto:shoka@everlore.com">Shoka</a> (7/27/00)</font></b></p>
			<font face="verdana" size="2">
<ul>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#Introduction">Introduction</a>:</font></li>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#The Blacksmiths Guide"><i>The
    Blacksmiths Guide to Arms And Armor</i>:</a></font></li>
  <li><a href="#How to make armor:"><font face="Verdana" size="2">How to make armor:</font></a></li>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#Banded armor table:">Banded armor
    table:</a></font></li>
</font>
  <li><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#weapons">Forged Weapons (NEW!)</font></li>
</ul></a>
			<font face="verdana" size="2">
<p><a name="Introduction">Introduction</a>:</p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">Now that you are a master of the creation of
most any recipe in the "Basic Blacksmith Recipe's" book, you are
prepared to for the next step in your blacksmithing career. The reason most
decide to become a blacksmith is simple, the profit that can be reaped by making
and selling banded armor. And you are now of the skill to construct your first pieces
of armor. Thus paving the way to your training completion, as a master
blacksmith.</font></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">If you are reading this part of the
blacksmithing guide "Advanced
Blacksmithing" we assume that you have
a skill of 50 in blacksmithing. You should not attempt to make any of the
recipes below until you are, simply because chances are you will fail are extremely
great, and fail will cost you a great expense of money and time. The first the
thing you should do is purchase the second blacksmithing book entitled "<i><a href="#The Blacksmiths Guide">The
Blacksmiths Guide to Arms And Armor</a></i>". With in this guide we do include
the text and recipes contained within the book, however as mentioned before it
is rumored that if you purchase the book and keep it visible in your inventory
(not in backpack etc) it will greatly increase you chances of success.</font></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">Here is the text of "<i>The Blacksmiths
Guide to Arms And Armor</i>:</font></p>
<p><i><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a name="The Blacksmiths Guide">The
Blacksmiths Guide to Arms And Armor</a></font></i></p>
<p><font size="2"><i><font face="Verdana">A detailed guide to the construction
of arms and armor for the experienced blacksmith.</font></i> <i><font face="Verdana">Reference
manual needed: The Guide to Blacksmithing.</font></i></font></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Required:</font></i></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">A
Forge</font></i></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Earth</font></i></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Fire</font></i></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Water</font></i></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Skill</font></i></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">On
Sizing and armor:</font></i></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Some
armor types must be sized to your client. There are three sizes of armor: Small,
Medium, and Large. Some races can wear more that one size of armor</font></i></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Barbarians,
Ogres and Trolls wear Large Armor</font></i></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2"><i><font face="Verdana">Barbarians,
Elves, Erudite, Half-</font></i><font face="Verdana"><i>Elves, and Humans wear
medium armor.</i></font></font></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2"><i><font face="Verdana">Dwarves
Elves Gnomes, and Halfings wear small armor.</font></i></font></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">Each
piece of Banded Armor can be sized can be sized to a small medium or large
client.</font></i></p>
<p style="line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><i><font face="Verdana" size="2">The
size of the armor s determined by the mold used. Each section of banded armor
requires a sheet of metal and a mold appropriate to the section of the body.
each also requires a flask of water to cool it."</font></i></p>
<p><a name="How to make armor:">How to make armor:</a></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">To make you first banded items just follow the
same process that you have been following through out the whole of your
blacksmith training. Place the proper ingredients with in the forge, and combine
them. </font></p>
<p><font face="Verdana" size="2">The first thing thing you should make is <a href="#Gorget">banded
gorgets</a>, gorgets require one gorget mold, one sheet of metal. and one flask
of water. After gorgets you should attempt  <a href="#Bracers and boots">bracers
and boots</a>. The <a href="#Banded armor table:">Banded armor
table</a> below is a rough guide at what you should attempt to make at what
level. </font></p>
<p align="center"><font face="Verdana" size="2"><a href="#Advanced Blacksmithing:">Top</a></font></p>
