				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hello. I am a master smith and I will tell you all the secrets ok? The BEST place to begin will be Freeport, the forge at the dwarven weapon shop is where you begin. Buy a bunch of sharpening stone and do rusty weapons until it says that its too easy for you to do. It will say something like that after you create the new Sharpened weapon. To sharpen click the forge, put the stone in, only 1 stone VERY IMPORTANT, and a rusty weapon and click 'combine' voila! Very easy. After that becomes too easy you can follow the Blacksmithing guide you can buy from any weapons shop in Norrath, try to make things from PG 1 until its too easy, then move on to the next thing to make in the book. In the end it will cost you about 300-400 platinum to become a Master Smith, it took me about 3 days PLAYED time..so remember to be patient. To tell you the truth I get more money off killing druids in the Karanas, but it's a wonderful skill and Guilds always welcome master smiths into their ranks. Anyway, good luck!<BR>
